HEADWORD: Semitic
<hw>Sem*it"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to
Shem or his descendants; belonging to that division of the Caucasian
race which includes the Arabs, Jews, and related races.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>Shemitic</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Semitic language</b></col>, <cd>a name used to designate
a group of Asiatic and African languages, some living and some dead,
namely: Hebrew and Ph⟦oe⟧nician, Aramaic, Assyrian, Arabic, Ethiopic
(Geez and Ampharic).</cd> <rj><au>Encyc. Brit.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Semitism</ent>⟦br⟧
